[This last provision is overkill if it means crew who stay on board and do not disembark are supposed to wear masks and gloves. There is zero danger of airborne transmission from ship to shore. Cotonou is close to Lagos, Nigeria on the West African coast; see map at http://www.beekeeping.com/countries/nigeria_map.jpg.

A CDC map of the EVD situation in Guinea, Sierra Leone and Liberia as of 4 Sep 2014 is at:
http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/resources/distribution-map-guinea-outbreak.html. - Mod.JW

